# {{PROJECT}}-deployment — Infrastructure

Docker Compose + nginx for {{PROJECT}}. Three environments live side-by-side: `prod/`, `dev/`, `dev-local/`, with shared nginx snippets under `shared/nginx/`.

> **Naming:** `dev-local/` is the zero-setup local stack (bundled DB, localhost). `dev/` is the remote deployment environment (hosted DB, on a VM, GHA auto-deploy on `dev`-branch push). `prod/` is deferred at bootstrap.

At bootstrap time, **only `dev/` and `dev-local/` are fully configured**. The `prod/` folder is stamped with `<FILL_IN>` placeholders — populate them by running `/configure-prod` from the workspace root when you're ready to publish.

## Layout

```
{{PROJECT}}-deployment/
├── prod/                       # production stack — DEFERRED at bootstrap
│   ├── docker-compose.yml
│   ├── docker-compose.logging.yml
│   ├── nginx/                  # prod CORS allowlist (<FILL_IN_PROD_DOMAIN>)
│   ├── env/                    # prod env files (gitignored, populated by /configure-prod)
│   └── .env                    # ports + grafana config (gitignored)
├── dev/                        # remote deployment stack — live at bootstrap
│   ├── docker-compose.yml
│   ├── nginx/                  # CORS for {{DEV_DOMAIN}}
│   ├── env/                    # remote dev env files (gitignored)
│   └── REBUILD.md              # from-zero VM runbook
├── dev-local/                  # local dev with bundled DB
│   ├── docker-compose.yml
│   ├── nginx/                  # CORS for localhost
│   ├── env/                    # local env files (gitignored)
│   └── env.example             # committed schema — cp to env/{{PROJECT}}-core.env, env/user-service.env
├── shared/
│   └── nginx/                  # mounted by every env's compose
│       ├── locations.conf      # routing rules (single source of truth)
│       ├── cors.conf
│       ├── proxy-params.conf
│       └── proxy-params-minimal.conf
├── grafana/, loki/, promtail/  # logging stack configs (referenced by prod/docker-compose.logging.yml)
├── .gitignore                  # **/env/*.env, prod/.env
└── .gitattributes              # LF on env files
```

## Environments at a glance

| | dev-local | dev (remote) | prod |
|---|---|---|---|
| Host | local | {{#VPS}}`{{DEV_SSH_HOST}}`{{/VPS}}{{#GCP}}`{{DEV_VM_NAME}}` ({{GCP_ZONE}}){{/GCP}} | TODO (`/configure-prod`) |
| External URL | `http://localhost:{{DEV_NGINX_PORT}}` | `https://{{DEV_DOMAIN}}` | TODO |
| Ingress | nginx ({{DEV_NGINX_PORT}}) → app | host Caddy → nginx (loopback 3030) → app | host Caddy → nginx → app |
| Database | bundled `{{DB}}` container | hosted ({{DB_HOSTING}}) | hosted ({{DB_HOSTING}}, dedicated cluster recommended) |
| Logging stack | not run | not run | run (`prod/docker-compose.logging.yml`) |
| Auto-deploy | n/a | GHA on `dev` push | GHA on `v*` tag push (when prod_ready). `main` push only publishes `:latest` — no deploy. |

## Routing (shared across all envs)

Defined in `shared/nginx/locations.conf` (single source of truth). Header versioning via `{{API_VERSION_HEADER}}: {{API_VERSION_DEFAULT}}` — no URL versioning.

```
{{API_BASE}}/auth     →  user-service
{{API_BASE}}/users    →  user-service
{{API_BASE}}/email    →  user-service
{{API_BASE}}/assets   →  user-service
{{API_BASE}}/*        →  {{PROJECT}}-core   (catch-all)
/api-docs/*           →  swagger-ui
/health               →  200 OK
```

## Image registry

Images are pulled from **{{IMAGE_REGISTRY}}** with prefix `{{IMAGE_PREFIX}}/`. Tags are passed inline at deploy time via env vars (`USER_SERVICE_TAG`, `CORE_TAG`, etc.) — format `sha-<short-git-sha>`.

## External network

`prod/` and `dev/` use the external bridge network `{{PROJECT}}-network` so the app stack and logging stack can co-exist from separate compose files. Create once per VM:

```bash
sudo docker network create {{PROJECT}}-network
```

`dev-local/` uses a self-contained `{{PROJECT}}-dev-network` — `docker compose up` works zero-setup.

## Env files

Stored per-env, **never committed** (matched by `**/env/*.env` in `.gitignore`).

| Env | Files |
|---|---|
| dev-local | `dev-local/env/{{PROJECT}}-core.env`, `dev-local/env/user-service.env` — `cp dev-local/env.example` to start |
| dev (remote) | `dev/env/{{PROJECT}}-core.env`, `dev/env/user-service.env` |
| prod | `prod/env/{{PROJECT}}-core.env`, `prod/env/user-service.env`, `prod/.env` (ports + grafana) |

LF line endings are mandatory on env files — `.gitattributes` enforces this.

## Common commands

```bash
# dev-local — local, zero setup
cd dev-local && docker compose up
cd dev-local && docker compose --profile tools up   # + mongo-express on :8081 (if db=mongo)

# dev — on the remote dev VM
sudo docker compose -f dev/docker-compose.yml up -d
sudo docker compose -f dev/docker-compose.yml logs -f

# prod — DEFERRED at bootstrap; populate prod/ first via /configure-prod
sudo docker compose -f prod/docker-compose.yml up -d
sudo docker compose -f prod/docker-compose.yml \
                    -f prod/docker-compose.logging.yml up -d
```

{{#VPS}}## Upload env files to the remote dev VM

```bash
scp -i {{DEV_SSH_KEY_PATH}} \
  dev/env/{{PROJECT}}-core.env dev/env/user-service.env \
  {{DEV_SSH_USER}}@{{DEV_SSH_HOST}}:/opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment/dev/env/
```

Then restart:
```bash
ssh -i {{DEV_SSH_KEY_PATH}} {{DEV_SSH_USER}}@{{DEV_SSH_HOST}} \
  "cd /opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment && sudo docker compose -f dev/docker-compose.yml up -d --force-recreate"
```
{{/VPS}}{{#GCP}}## Upload env files to the remote dev VM (GCP IAP)

```powershell
gcloud compute scp --tunnel-through-iap --zone={{GCP_ZONE}} `
  .\dev\env\{{PROJECT}}-core.env .\dev\env\user-service.env `
  {{DEV_VM_NAME}}:/opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment/dev/env/
```

Then restart:
```bash
gcloud compute ssh {{DEV_VM_NAME}} --zone={{GCP_ZONE}} --tunnel-through-iap \
  --command="cd /opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment && sudo docker compose -f dev/docker-compose.yml up -d --force-recreate"
```
{{/GCP}}

## When to update this repo

- Adding a new service to a stack
- Changing port mappings
- Modifying nginx routing rules (touch `shared/nginx/locations.conf` once — applies to all envs)
- Updating CORS allowlist for one env (touch only that env's `nginx/nginx.conf`)
- Resource limit changes
- Env variable schema (coordinate with the consuming repo)

Feature changes in `{{PROJECT}}-core` / `user-service` / `{{PROJECT}}-web*` do **not** require changes here — they ship via Docker images and the GHA deploy workflows handle the image bump.

## Production setup

Deferred at bootstrap. Run `/configure-prod` from the workspace root when ready to publish — that skill will:

1. Ask for prod domain, prod SSH/VM details, prod DB connection strings
2. Populate the `<FILL_IN_*>` placeholders across `prod/`
3. Stamp `prod/REBUILD.md` (the from-zero prod runbook)
4. Add `release.yml` GHA workflow for tag-based prod releases
5. Wire prod secrets to the relevant code repos
